This paper discusses the design and implementation of a secure multiparty authentication framework for dynamic interaction in cloud environments. The paper focuses on security challenges and authentication processes, which are typically discussed in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of data analytics services, which falls under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper addresses the challenges of collaboration and orchestration of services, which are typically discussed in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applicability of the proposed framework to the emerging Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
